# Fintech Compliance

- Every page mentioning payment processing must include:
  "Charm Payments is a payment facilitator, not a bank. Payment
  processing services are provided through our licensed acquiring
  bank partner. Merchant funds are subject to the terms of the
  Merchant Agreement."

- Every page mentioning banking or deposits (Charm Wallet) must
  include: "Charm is not a bank. Banking services are provided by
  a sponsor bank, Member FDIC. Deposits are FDIC insured up to
  $250,000."

- Every form collecting SSN must include:
  "We collect your SSN to verify your identity and prevent fraud.
  It is never stored on our servers."

- Privacy Policy and Terms links must appear on every page with a form.
- Never use the word "free" if there are hidden costs.
- Never use "bank" to describe Charm without the disclaimer nearby.
- All marketing language must be clear and truthful.
- FTC truth-in-advertising standards apply to all copy.
